<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="lectotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Lectotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">(designated by Davis in Notes Roy. Bot. Gard. Edinburgh 22: 164. 1957): locality, date and collector unknown, Herb. Linnaeus No. 580.4 (LINN!).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, PH" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="163 - 171" refId="B30" refString="Davis, PH, 1957. New turkish species of Tunica, Velezia and Potentilla. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 22: 163 - 171" title="New turkish species of Tunica, Velezia and Potentilla." volume="22" year="1957">Davis (1957)</bibRefCitation>
had pointed out the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Tunica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tunica cretica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Tunica cretica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Fisch. &amp; C.A.Mey. (basionym: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fassou &amp; Korotkova &amp; Nersesyan &amp; Koch &amp; Dimopoulos &amp; Borsch" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Fassou &amp; Korotkova &amp; Nersesyan &amp; Koch &amp; Dimopoulos &amp; Borsch" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Saponaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saponaria cretica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Saponaria cretica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.) had been misapplied, whereas in fact the type of the name (the specimen in LINN) is an annual species that was later named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fassou &amp; Korotkova &amp; Nersesyan &amp; Koch &amp; Dimopoulos &amp; Borsch" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Fassou &amp; Korotkova &amp; Nersesyan &amp; Koch &amp; Dimopoulos &amp; Borsch" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Tunica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tunica pachygona" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachygona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Tunica pachygona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fisch. &amp; C.A.Mey. Accordingly, the correct name in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Dianthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dianthus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Dianthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. pachygonus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachygonus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">D. pachygonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new combination published here because the epithet of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fassou &amp; Korotkova &amp; Nersesyan &amp; Koch &amp; Dimopoulos &amp; Borsch" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Fassou &amp; Korotkova &amp; Nersesyan &amp; Koch &amp; Dimopoulos &amp; Borsch" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Saponaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saponaria cretica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Saponaria cretica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is preoccupied in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Dianthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dianthus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Dianthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. creticus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">D. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tausch. which is now treated as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Dianthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dianthus fruticosus subsp. creticus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="fruticosus" subSpecies="creticus">Dianthus fruticosus subsp. creticus</taxonomicName>
(Tausch) Runemark.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
